node.title: Sunken boats in Northland marina to be refloated - Harbourmaster
node.description: Some of the sunken boats in Northland's T큰t큰k훮k훮 Marina could be refloated today and tomorrow.
node.content:
["Some of the sunken boats in Northland's Tūtūkākā Marina could be refloated today and tomorrow.", "", "
Boats were damaged at Tūtūkākā Marina in Far North overnight of 15 January after strong tidal surges as a result of remnants from Cyclone Cody and the volcanic eruption in Tonga. Photo: RNZ / Sam Olley
", "Salvage experts and insurance assessors have been heading north to the facility which was hit by a wave generated by Tonga's volcanic explosion.", "About six vessels have sunk but there could be more smaller run-abouts submerged and not yet found.", "Northland regional harbourmaster Jim Lyall said damage to the marina could have been worse.", "Lyall said many boats were still trapped in the marina by pontoons twisting and blocking exits.", "Authorities will start freeing the boats once salavage of the sunken vessels is finished."]
